Yum! I've made this a few times, and it's always been great, but last night I found I was low on honey. Being Canadian, the first substitute I thought of was maple syrup. It made a very different, and very delicious, twist to this. I think I might try it with a good lean ham sausage, such as Mondare or a quality Kielbasa.

